Each letter has its ‘time,' or ‘timesss Thus a short vowel

has the time of one beat (mora); a long vowel, of two beats; a single consonant, of a half beat; a double consonant, of one beat. Theoretically, therefore, a syllable may have as many as three, or even four, tempora ,· but practically only two are recognized. All over two are disregarded and each syllable is simply counted ‘short ’ (one beat) or ‘long' (two beats),
